#: ../../ACS.rst:271
msgid ""
"In this strategy all configuration of nodes of the same PubSub service "
"JID is done by the same node of a cluster which is dynamically selected "
"based on hash of service JID and number of connected nodes within "
"cluster. After any change to node configuration is done, then node "
"established for processing manipulation of this particular PubSub node is"
" notified about details of the PubSub node and detailed changes made to "
"it’s configuration. Remaining nodes do not require to know about changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:273 ../../ACS.rst:319
msgid ""
"Presences sent from users to PubSub service will be handled on the local "
"node of the cluster and then distributed to every node of a cluster as "
"events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:275 ../../ACS.rst:321
msgid ""
"Messages sent from users to PubSub service will be handled on the local "
"node of the cluster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:277
msgid ""
"Presence and IQ stanzas will be processed according to rules outlined "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:279 ../../ACS.rst:327
msgid "Rules of processing packets:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:281
msgid ""
"``presence`` - packets are processed on the local cluster node and then "
"other cluster nodes are notified about changed presence as each cluster "
"node is responsible for handling different PubSub nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:283 ../../ACS.rst:331
msgid "``message`` - is always processed locally"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:285 ../../ACS.rst:333
msgid ""
"``iq`` - cluster node which will process this packet is selected based on"
" following rules:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:287 ../../ACS.rst:335
msgid "CAPS query responses will be processed on the local node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:289 ../../ACS.rst:337
msgid "non-PubSub packets (no ``pubsub`` subelement) are processed on local node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:291
msgid ""
"PubSub related packets without PubSub node name or packets that change "
"PubSub node configuration (and contains ``node`` name and one of the "
"following subelements: ``create``, ``configure``, ``default``, "
"``delete``) are processed on cluster node selected on hashcode derived "
"from ``to`` attribute (service JID) and number of cluster nodes (this is "
"done deal with concurrency issues between configuration changes)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:293
msgid ""
"remaining PubSub packets (non-configuration and containing ``node`` name)"
" are processed on cluster node selected based on ``to`` attribute of "
"packet and name of PubSub node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:297
msgid ""
"This strategy for every packet should force processing of packet on only "
"one cluster node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:301
msgid ""
"This strategy will react on PubSub configuration node change and will "
"send notification to cluster node responsible for processing items for "
"PubSub node (selected based on ``to`` attribute of packet, name of PubSub"
" node) to trigger cached PubSub node configuration refresh"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:305
msgid ""
"Result of packets generated on remote node should **not be** filtered, so"
" if packet from one cluster node was forwarded to other cluster node for "
"processing, then response packet should not be filtered when this PubSub "
"clustering strategy is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:309
msgid "ACS-PubSub Clustered Node Strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:313
msgid ""
"This strategy is used by default by Tigase ACS - PubSub component in "
"which each PubSub node is handled on every cluster node but each cluster "
"node will contain only partial information about user connections. This "
"way strategy is better suited for deployments with PubSub nodes having a "
"lot of subscribers. The benefit of using ClusterNodeStrategy in this case"
" is reduced network traffic on cluster connections, as most of "
"notifications and retrieval of items will be handled on the same cluster "
"node to which user is connected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:317
msgid ""
"In this strategy almost all packets are processed on the local cluster "
"node. Only packets related to settings default options (such as pubsub "
"packets containing subelements ``options`` or ``default``) will be "
"forwared to all cluster nodes and processed on each of them. If packets "
"will result in the node configuration, subscriptions or affiliations "
"changes other nodes will be notified to refresh node "
"configuration/subscriptions/affiliations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:323
msgid ""
"If every other IQ stanza sent to PubSub service which is does not change "
"configuration of a node and is item publication stanza then this stanza "
"will always be processed on local node (as data retrieval/removal may be "
"done only on one node as items are not cached)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:325
msgid ""
"IQ stanzas which are stanza responsible for publication are processed on "
"the local cluster node. In this case PubSub will able to properly send "
"notifications (as notification are generated always on local user node, "
"if user is connected, which reduces cluster network traffic)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:329
msgid ""
"``presence`` - packets are delivered to every cluster node as each "
"cluster node is responsible for handling different PubSub nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:339
msgid ""
"PubSub related packets without PubSub node name are processed on the "
"local node. If packets will result in the node configuration changes, "
"other nodes will be notified to refresh node configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:341
msgid ""
"PubSub related packets containing subelements named ``options`` or "
"``default`` will be forwarded to all connected cluster nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:343
msgid ""
"remaining PubSub packets are processed on the local cluster node. If "
"packets will result in the node configuration changes, other nodes will "
"be notified to refresh node configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:347
msgid ""
"This strategy will react to PubSub configuration node change and will "
"send notification to every cluster node (as every cluster node is "
"responsible for processing items for every PubSub node) to refresh "
"particular PubSub node configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:351
msgid ""
"Result of processing of packets generated on remote node should **be** "
"filtered if packet was also processed on local node, so if packet from "
"one cluster node was forwarded to other cluster node for processing but "
"was not processed locally, then response packet should be filtered when "
"this PubSub clustering strategy is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:354
msgid "In a nutshell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:356
msgid ""
"``Clustered Node Strategy`` distributes processing of nodes across "
"cluster by processing all requests locally - each cluster node has "
"complete knowledge of all PubSub nodes and processed requests for all of "
"them, but generates notifications only for users connected to this "
"particular node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ACS.rst:358
msgid ""
"``Partitioned Strategy`` assigns PubSub node to cluster node and handle "
"all processing on that particular cluster node (configuration change, "
"generating notification packets)."
msgstr ""

